explanation.en:
This patient with exertional dyspnea, fatigue, conjunctival pallor, and a systolic ejection murmur has symptomatic anemia. The peripheral blood smear findings of macrocytosis (abnormally large red blood cells) and a hypersegmented neutrophil {{exhibit_2}} indicate likely megaloblastic anemia. This condition sometimes arises in older individuals who take antacids for gastroesophageal reflux disease, as gastric acid is required for proper vitamin B₁₂ absorption.

Vitamin B₁₂ acts as a cofactor in the recycling of 5-methyl-tetrahydrofolate to tetrahydrofolate (reduced form of folate), which serves as a one-carbon donor in the synthesis of amino acids, purines, and thymidine monophosphate. Therefore, folate or vitamin B₁₂ deficiency reduces available purines and thymidine, which impairs DNA synthesis and causes cell cycle arrest (in S-phase) or apoptotic cell death.

Hematopoietic cells are primarily affected due to their high replication rate. In these cells, nuclear division slows relative to cytoplasmic maturation (nuclear-cytoplasmic dyssynchrony), which results in megaloblastic changes (eg, macrocytosis, hypersegmented neutrophils); in addition, increased apoptosis causes anemia and mild thrombocytopenia/leukopenia.

Although vitamin B₁₂ deficiency also commonly presents with neurologic findings (eg, symmetric paresthesia, gait problems), patients can develop significant hematologic changes with no noticeable neuropsychiatric symptoms.

(Choice B) Iron deficiency anemia is associated with impaired production of heme; however, peripheral blood smear would show microcytosis (not macrocytosis), and hypersegmented neutrophils would not be seen. {{exhibit_3}}

(Choice C) Chronic kidney disease can reduce production of erythropoietin in peritubular fibroblasts of the kidney, which causes normocytic anemia due to reduced erythropoiesis. However, leukopenia and thrombocytopenia are not typically seen, and peripheral blood smear would not show megaloblastic changes. {{exhibit_4}}

(Choice D) Aplastic anemia is associated with destruction of hematopoietic stem cells and replacement of the bone marrow with fat cells. Although patients usually have pancytopenia, peripheral blood smear would not show hypersegmented neutrophils. {{exhibit_5}}

(Choice E) Primary myelofibrosis is a myeloproliferative neoplasm that results in fibrosis of the bone marrow. Anemia is common but patients usually have dacrocytes (tear-drop red blood cells) and nucleated red blood cells on peripheral blood smear, not macrocytosis, and hypersegmented neutrophils. {{exhibit_6}}

(Choice F) Aortic stenosis can cause traumatic hemolysis due to red blood cell shearing. However, peripheral smear generally shows schistocytes, and thrombocytopenia/leukopenia would be unusual.

Educational objective:
Vitamin B₁₂ is an essential cofactor in the recycling of 5-methyl-tetrahydrofolate to tetrahydrofolate, which is required for amino acid, purine, and thymidine synthesis. Deficiency primarily affects hematopoiesis and is marked by impaired nuclear maturation, leading to macrocytic red blood cells and hypersegmented neutrophils; increased apoptosis often also leads to anemia and mild thrombocytopenia/leukopenia.

explanation.zh:
该患者出现劳力性呼吸困难、疲劳、结膜苍白和收缩期喷射性杂音，提示有症状性贫血。外周血涂片结果显示大细胞性红细胞增多症（异常大的红细胞）和多分叶中性粒细胞{{exhibit_2}}，提示巨幼细胞性贫血。这种情况有时会发生在因胃食管反流病服用抗酸药的老年人身上，因为胃酸是维生素B₁₂适当吸收所必需的。

维生素B₁₂是5-甲基四氢叶酸再循环为四氢叶酸（叶酸的还原形式）的辅助因子，后者作为一碳供体参与氨基酸、嘌呤和胸腺嘧啶单磷酸盐的合成。因此，叶酸或维生素B₁₂缺乏会减少可利用的嘌呤和胸腺嘧啶，从而损害DNA合成，导致细胞周期停滞（S期）或细胞凋亡死亡。

造血细胞由于其高复制率而受到主要影响。在这些细胞中，核分裂相对于细胞质成熟减慢（核-胞质不同步），导致巨幼细胞性改变（如大细胞性红细胞增多症、多分叶中性粒细胞）；此外，细胞凋亡增加会导致贫血和轻度血小板减少症/白细胞减少症。

尽管维生素B₁₂缺乏症也常表现为神经系统表现（如对称性感觉异常、步态问题），但患者可能会出现明显的血液学改变，而没有明显的神经精神症状。

(选项B) 缺铁性贫血与血红素生成受损有关；然而，外周血涂片会显示小细胞性红细胞增多症（而非大细胞性红细胞增多症），并且不会出现多分叶中性粒细胞。{{exhibit_3}}

(选项C) 慢性肾脏病可减少肾脏肾小管周围成纤维细胞中促红细胞生成素的生成，这会导致由于红细胞生成减少而出现的正细胞性贫血。然而，通常不会出现白细胞减少症和血小板减少症，并且外周血涂片不会显示巨幼细胞性改变。{{exhibit_4}}

(选项D) 再生障碍性贫血与造血干细胞破坏以及骨髓被脂肪细胞替代有关。尽管患者通常有全血细胞减少症，但外周血涂片不会显示多分叶中性粒细胞。{{exhibit_5}}

(选项E) 原发性骨髓纤维化是一种骨髓增生性肿瘤，导致骨髓纤维化。贫血很常见，但患者通常在外周血涂片上有多形红细胞（泪滴状红细胞）和有核红细胞，而不是大细胞性红细胞增多症和多分叶中性粒细胞。{{exhibit_6}}

(选项F) 主动脉瓣狭窄可因红细胞剪切而引起创伤性溶血。然而，外周血涂片通常显示裂红细胞，并且血小板减少症/白细胞减少症是不常见的。

教育目标：
维生素B₁₂是5-甲基四氢叶酸再循环为四氢叶酸（氨基酸、嘌呤和胸腺嘧啶合成所需）的重要辅助因子。缺乏主要影响造血，其特征是核成熟受损，导致大细胞性红细胞和多分叶中性粒细胞；细胞凋亡增加也常导致贫血和轻度血小板减少症/白细胞减少症。
